	description="Oakland infertility counseling and Brainspotting therapy. Compassionate support for assisted reproduction, IVF, pregnancy loss, and fertility journey. LMFT specializing in reproductive mental health."
>
	<header class="header">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="header-content">
				<div class="logo">
					<h1 class="logo-text">Oakland Brainspotting Therapy</h1>
					<p class="tagline">Brain-Based Healing in the Heart of Oakland</p>
				</div>
				<nav class="nav">
					<a href="/">Home</a>
					<a href="/trauma">Trauma</a>
					<a href="/grief">Grief</a>
					<a href="/about-megan">About Megan</a>
				</nav>
			</div>
		</div>
	</header>

	<section class="hero">
		<div class="hero-overlay"></div>
		<div class="container hero-content">
			<h1 class="hero-title">Infertility Counseling with Brainspotting in Oakland</h1>
			<p class="hero-subtitle">Compassionate support for assisted reproduction, pregnancy loss, and your fertility journey</p>

			<div class="hero-cta">
				<ConsultationButton variant="primary" location="infertility_hero" />
				<a href="#emotional-journey" class="btn btn-secondary">Learn More</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<main id="main-content">
		<section id="emotional-journey" class="section section-light">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>The Emotional Journey of Infertility</h2>
				<div class="content-flow">
					<p class="lead">
						Infertility is one of the most emotionally challenging experiences a person or couple can face. It touches every part of your life—your body, your relationships, your sense of self, your hopes for the future.
					</p>
					<p>The fertility journey often includes intense emotions like grief, loss, anger, isolation, shame, hope, and disappointment—sometimes all in the same day.</p>

					<h3>IVF/IUI Emotional Toll</h3>
					<p>Assisted reproduction involves intense physical, emotional, and financial investment. The two-week waits, the hormone fluctuations, the procedures, the constant uncertainty—it all takes a profound toll on your nervous system and mental health.</p>

					<h3>Pregnancy Loss & Grief</h3>
					<p>Miscarriage, chemical pregnancies, failed transfers—each loss is real and deserves to be mourned. Yet many people face these losses in isolation, without adequate support or recognition of their pain.</p>

					<h3>Relationship Strain</h3>
					<p>Infertility can put immense pressure on relationships. Partners may grieve differently, communicate in different ways, or have different ideas about how to move forward. The intimacy and joy that sex once brought can become medicalized and stressful.</p>

					<h3>Isolation & Shame</h3>
					<p>Many people struggling with infertility feel isolated—watching friends and family announce pregnancies, feeling like your body has betrayed you, wondering if you'll ever have the family you've hoped for.</p>

					<h3>Hope & Disappointment Cycles</h3>
					<p>The fertility journey is a roller coaster of hope and disappointment. Each treatment cycle brings new hope, followed by the potential crushing disappointment of a negative result. Learning to hold both hope and grief is one of the hardest parts.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section section-accent">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>How Brainspotting Helps with Infertility</h2>
				<div class="content-flow">
					<p class="lead">Brainspotting offers a way to process the deep grief, trauma, and stress that comes with infertility—releasing what your body has been holding so you can move forward with more resilience and peace.</p>

					<h3>Processing Grief at Depth</h3>
					<p>Each pregnancy loss, each failed cycle, each disappointment leaves an imprint on your nervous system. Brainspotting allows you to access and release this stored grief in a safe, supported way.</p>

					<h3>Releasing Trauma from Losses</h3>
					<p>For many, pregnancy loss or traumatic fertility experiences create trauma responses. Brainspotting helps your brain and body process these experiences so they no longer trigger such intense reactions.</p>

					<h3>Nervous System Support</h3>
					<p>The constant stress of the fertility journey keeps your nervous system in fight-flight mode. Brainspotting helps regulate your nervous system, bringing you back to a state where healing and hope can coexist.</p>

					<h3>Building Resilience</h3>
					<p>While Brainspotting can't control the outcome of your fertility journey, it can help you build the emotional resilience to navigate whatever comes—to hold hope while acknowledging pain, to care for yourself through uncertainty.</p>

					<h3>Connecting with Your Body</h3>
					<p>Infertility can make you feel at war with your body. Brainspotting can help you reconnect with compassion and care for yourself, even when your body isn't doing what you want it to.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section section-light">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>Oakland Fertility Landscape</h2>
				<div class="content-flow">
					<p>The Bay Area has numerous fertility clinics and resources, but the emotional support often lags behind the medical technology. Many people receive excellent medical care while struggling emotionally in isolation.</p>
					<p>As someone who provides psychological evaluations for California fertility clinics, I understand the fertility world from both the clinical and deeply personal perspectives. I know the language, the procedures, the challenges you're facing.</p>

					<h3>Why Specialized Support Matters</h3>
					<p>Not all therapists understand the unique challenges of infertility. You need someone who gets it—someone who won't minimize your pain, who understands the medical process, and who can support you through the ups and downs.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section section-accent">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>What to Expect in Infertility Counseling</h2>
				<div class="content-flow">
					<h3>Flexible Session Structure</h3>
					<p>Sessions can focus on processing grief from losses, managing anxiety during treatment cycles, working through relationship challenges, or simply having a safe space to express everything you're feeling.</p>

					<h3>Working Alongside Fertility Treatment</h3>
					<p>Therapy can happen concurrently with your fertility treatment. In fact, having emotional support during active treatment can help you navigate the process with more resilience.</p>

					<h3>Partner Support Available</h3>
					<p>I offer couples counseling for partners navigating infertility together. We can work on communication, processing grief as a couple, and finding ways to support each other through this journey.</p>

					<p>Whether you're just beginning fertility treatment, in the middle of multiple cycles, processing pregnancy loss, or considering next steps, therapy can provide the emotional support and healing you need.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section section-cta">
			<div class="container cta-content">
				<h2>Ready for Support on Your Fertility Journey?</h2>
				<p class="lead">Schedule your free 15-minute consultation to learn how infertility counseling and Brainspotting can support you through this challenging time.</p>
				<div class="cta-buttons">
					<ConsultationButton variant="primary" size="large" location="infertility_cta" />
				</div>
				<p class="cta-note">Serving Oakland, Berkeley, Alameda, and throughout the Bay Area • In-person and telehealth available</p>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>

